{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"71c25e9f-506f-4331-ac4c-0d0605e54d70","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_Q4Nx46dPm9ELu8sGqGDqsd","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Answering MSTest SDK question"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_teFDAQZNVsv6vT9DvQBaxq","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-b28a31c42fe044deac45bdf05f9e343f"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-b28a31c42fe044deac45bdf05f9e343f."}],"interactionId":"bc633593-635f-4068-8079-106d70f88945","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically related to test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes.\n\nLet me look at the files in the current directory to see if there's relevant context, but this is likely a question I can answer from my knowledge about MSTest SDK changes.\n\nThe key change: Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8 (or around that version), Microsoft introduced the \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" (MTP) as the default test runner. However, in MSTest.Sdk 3.x, VSTest was still supported/default. In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the VSTest compatibility layer was removed by default.\n \nIn version 4.0 and later, MSTest switched to Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default runner, which means vstest.console can no longer discover tests unless you explicitly restore VSTest support. You can either migrate to using `dotnet test` with the new testing platform, run the test executable directly, or add a property to re-enable the VSTest compatibility layer.","outputTokens":655,"requestId":"9827:C2332:135A96F:185A3A0:69FFF664"},"id":"677b7b98-cf72-4862-aea3-61918b7f1b2d","timestamp":"2026-05-10T03:07:31.097Z","parentId":"55f64cc6-b46b-4030-944e-155e430988f2"}
