{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"256fdcc0-5de1-42a1-bc1b-bd2eb644d060","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest adapter by default.** It now exclusively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the runner. Since `vstest.console` relies on the VSTest adapter (`MSTest.TestAdapter`) to discover tests, it no longer works out of the box.\n\n**Your options:**\n\n1. **Switch your CI to use `dotnet test`** (which supports MTP natively in .NET 9+ SDK), or run the test executable directly:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   # or\n   ./TestProject --list-tests\n   ```\n\n2. **Re-enable the VSTest bridge** if you must keep `vstest.console`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nOption 1 is the recommended path forward since MTP is now the default and offers better performance.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bc633593-635f-4068-8079-106d70f88945","outputTokens":235,"requestId":"981A:23633C:1364D2C:1862076:69FFF675"},"id":"b3dac860-90b7-438d-b92f-1e04acbc35db","timestamp":"2026-05-10T03:07:39.014Z","parentId":"8da39f9a-8746-462c-9a4d-0b26c4d15653"}
